Guinea to Complete Review of Mining Laws in June, Minister Says

-- B y   O u g n a   C a m a r a
-- 
2011-05-12T22:02:37Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-12/guinea-to-complete-review-of-mining-laws-in-june-minister-says.html
Guinea  will complete a review of its
mining laws in June, the minister of mines and geology, Mohamed
Lamine Fofana, said in an interview today.   The review will help cancel more than 75 percent of
fictitious licenses, Fofana said today in Conakry, the capital.
Separately, he declined to comment on talks with  Vale SA (VALE3)  about a
halted railway project.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Vivek Shankar at 
 vshankar3@bloomberg.net  